        public void deleteExecution(String executionIdentifier,
                            DeleteExecutionConfiguration body)
                     throws ApiException
        Delete an execution. This will kill the underlying processes (if possible) and free all resources associated with this execution (depending of the configuration given in as body input).
        Parameters:
        executionIdentifier - (required)
        body - delete configuration (optional)
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body

      • listExecutions

        public List<Execution> listExecutions()
                               throws ApiException
        list all execution Ids in the platform which are ordered in decreasing submission time. All the executions that were launched by the user must be returned. It is up to the platform to return executions that the user did not launch. When studyIdentifier is present, all the executions that the user launched in the study must be returned.
        Returns:
        List<Execution>
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body

      • listExecutionsWithHttpInfo

        public ApiResponse<List<Execution>> listExecutionsWithHttpInfo()
                                                        throws ApiException
        list all execution Ids in the platform which are ordered in decreasing submission time. All the executions that were launched by the user must be returned. It is up to the platform to return executions that the user did not launch. When studyIdentifier is present, all the executions that the user launched in the study must be returned.
        Returns:
        ApiResponse<List<Execution>>
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body

      • listExecutionsAsync

        public com.squareup.okhttp.Call listExecutionsAsync(ApiCallback<List<Execution>> callback)
                                             throws ApiException
        (asynchronously) list all execution Ids in the platform which are ordered in decreasing submission time. All the executions that were launched by the user must be returned.       • listPipelines

        public List<Pipeline> listPipelines(String studyIdentifier)
                             throws ApiException
        All the pipelines that the user can execute must be returned. It is up to the platform to return pipelines that the user cannot execute. When studyIdentifier is present, all the pipelines that the user can execute in the study must be returned. In this case, execution rights denote the rights to execute the pipeline in the study.
        Parameters:
        studyIdentifier - (optional)
        Returns:
        List<Pipeline>
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body

      • listPipelinesWithHttpInfo

        public ApiResponse<List<Pipeline>> listPipelinesWithHttpInfo(String studyIdentifier)
                                                      throws ApiException
        All the pipelines that the user can execute must be returned. It is up to the platform to return pipelines that the user cannot execute. When studyIdentifier is present, all the pipelines that the user can execute in the study must be returned. In this case, execution rights denote the rights to execute the pipeline in the study.
        Parameters:
        studyIdentifier - (optional)
        Returns:
        ApiResponse<List<Pipeline>>
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
